  "text": "The Kafka consumer heartbeat session timeout mechanism is implemented through a multi-file architecture. The session timeout threshold is defined in CommonClientConfigs.java with the SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG constant, representing the consumer configuration key 'session.timeout.ms'. This value is read into GroupRebalanceConfig.java as the sessionTimeoutMs field (line 52 reads from CommonClientConfigs.SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG). In Heartbeat.java, the sessionTimer is initialized with this sessionTimeoutMs value (line 52), and the sessionTimeoutExpired() method (line 119-122) checks if this timer has expired by calling sessionTimer.isExpired(). When a heartbeat response is received, receiveHeartbeat() (line 98-103) resets the session timeout timer. The heartbeat session timeout check occurs in the consumer's background heartbeat thread, implemented in AbstractCoordinator.java. The HeartbeatThread class (line 1454+) continuously runs a loop that checks heartbeat.sessionTimeoutExpired(now) at line 1513. When this check returns true, indicating that no successful heartbeat response was received within the session timeout period, the code calls markCoordinatorUnknown() at line 1516 with the message 'session timed out without receiving a heartbeat response'. This causes the consumer group coordinator to be marked as unavailable, resulting in the consumer dropping its group membership. The markCoordinatorUnknown() method (line 1004-1029) logs an info message and disconnects from the coordinator, forcing the consumer to rediscover and rejoin the group. This is the mechanism by which Kafka consumer groups drop membership when heartbeat session timeouts occur during the consumer polling loop."
}

